In the Matter of ANNIN & CO. (a New York Corporation), Debtor. Maurice De Sedle, Claimant-Appellant, Annin & Co., Debtor-Appellee. No. 19. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Nov. 15, 1937. Shaine & Weinrib, of New York City (David W. Kahn, Edward C. Weinrib, Edward ■ J. Mallin, and Nathan Siegel, all of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. Zalkin & Cohen, of New York City (Barney B. Fensterstock, Harry Zalkin, and Israel Akselrod, all of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before MANTON, AUGUSTUS N. HAND, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Order affirmed.
